		<td valign="top">
		<img src="images/page14.gif">
		<p><br>
A loon that laughed on Echo Lake
<br>
eluded me, but once, alone
<br>
in dismal twilight mist, I saw
<br>
his head pop up beside my boat&#8212;
<br>
he stared with shrewd, demonic eyes
<br>
until his slippery serpent shape
<br>
insinuated inky depths.
<br>
He rose and dove repeatedly,
<br>
and then abruptly disappeared.
<br>
Under his spell, I worked the oars
<br>
and circled twice around the lake,
<br>
convinced my wits would win this game.
<br>
But at his cry, I saw him bobbing
<br>
on my crazed, reflected face.
<br>
As we divined each other's mind
<br>
beneath embracing lunar light,
<br>
our laughter echoed through the night.
<br>
		</p>
		<br>
		<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('larosa')">by Ralph C. La Rosa</a>
		</td></tr></table>
